EnLink maintains a corporate Emergency Preparedness and Response Plan (EPRP) that provides guidance for emergencies expected at all EnLink facilities, including the Riverside Plant, as well as additional safety information. The Riverside Plant also maintains a site-specific Emergency Action Plan.  In addition, operating procedures and equipment design codes and standards associated with the operations at the Facility are maintained. Furthermore, the facility has coordinated the emergency response with the Ascension Parish Office of Emergency Preparedness (OEP) and the Geismar Fire Department.  For these reasons, the Riverside Plant meets the exceptions listed in 40 CFR 68.90(b), and therefore the Facility is not required to have the Emergency Response Program as described in 40 CFR 68.95.  



A site map, MSDSs, and a list of chemicals kept on-site are maintained at the Facility. Complete details on the Emergency Response Program required under the PSM Rules are included in the Riverside Plant's PSM Plan, which is kept on-site as a separate document.   



PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY



The Facility last completed a Process Hazard Analysis (PHA) in January 2008 to assess potential areas to improve safety at the Facility.  The final action item from the PHA was completed in August 2009.
